The paper is about image captioning, which is a task in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves attention mechanisms and language generation, which are also relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also introduces a novel module for improving model performance, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the experimental results are evaluated on the Microsoft COCO benchmark, which is a popular dataset in multimedia research (cs.MM).
